Jeff Wicks, News24 Paramedics on the scene of the accident. (Jeff Wicks, News24) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Ntuzuma - The beginning of the school year was mired by tragedy on Wednesday&nbsp;when four scholars, three boys and a girl, were killed in a minibus taxi accident on Ingcebo Road.The ages of the children was not immediately knownIt is understood that a Durban Transport bus and a minibus carrying school children collided head on near the Mbondwe Road junction.The force of impact sheared the taxi in half, and pushed it to the roadside.Paramedics scrambled to stabilize a critically injured teenage boy, working in amidst the bodies of the dead.Twelve others were injured and were transported by ambulance to local clinics and hospitals.Officials from the eThekwini Municipality were at the scene to initiate an investigation into the crash. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.